The South African Police Service is appealing to anyone who might be looking for a missing person in Thembalethu, George, in the Western Cape, to come forward and assist to identify the body found next to a river.
Police said the body, which they can not determine as male or female, was found next to the river at the back of Silvertown, Zone 6 Thembalethu on Saturday, 27 January, at 1pm.
A statement from the police said: “The body was dressed in a brown T-shirt, blue jeans and black shoes. The police are investigating an inquest docket. The police are not sure whether it is a body of a male or female”.
Anyone with information is urged to contact Constable Luthando Janjtie of Thembalethu Detectives at 044 802 8934.
– African News Agency (ANA)
